Simple web stack for www.foobar.com

User -> Browser requests: www.foobar.com -> DNS:(www.foobar.com -> 8.8.8.8)
-> (Server IP: 8.8.8.8) -> Nginx Web Server ->Application Server -> Application Files -> MySQL Database.

Components
- Server: a physical or virtual machine that provides resources and runs services.
- Domain name: a human-readable name used to reach the server instead of an IP address.
- DNS record (www): an A record that points www.foobar.com to the server IP address.
- Web server: receives HTTP requests, serves static content, and forwards dynamic requests to the application server.
- Application server: runs the application code and generates dynamic content.
- Database: stores and manages persistent application data.
- Communication protocol: the server and the user’s computer communicate over HTTP through the network.

Issues
Single Point of Failure (SPOF): if the only server goes down, the entire website becomes inaccessible.
Downtime during maintenance: actions like restarting the web server or deploying updates can temporarily take the site offline.
Lack of scalability: the system cannot efficiently handle increased traffic since it relies on just one server and cannot scale horizontally.